page.title: 01N.E.FLEETWOOD and KNOTT END.
page.content: This area includes Fleetwood container port and the village of Knott End-on-Sea, bounded to the north west by Fleetwood's North Wharf and to the north east by Preesall Sands, while its south west boundary lies in the residential area to the east of Fleetwood Golf Links and its south eastern boundary looks eastwards to the five small lakes of south west Preesall. The River Wyre separates Fleetwood town from Knott End village, and as the ferry carries people but not cars, Fleetwood drivers have to travel through Thornton and across the Shard Toll Bridge to reach Knott End via Hambleton and Stalmine. Both places are sea-side resorts, but Fleetwood is linked to industry whereas Knott End-on-Sea is linked to farming.
